    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `Bun.INI`:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**6 files to touch** (1 new, 5 modified):\n\n### New File: `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\nA self-contained INI parse + stringify implementation:\n- **`create()`** — builds a JS object with `parse` and `stringify` methods, identical pattern to `JSON5Object.zig`\n- **`parse()`** — reads line-by-line: skips `; #` comments, handles `[section]` headers (creates nested JS objects), handles `key = value` pairs; uses `JSValue.createEmptyObject` and `ZigString.fromUTF8` to build the result directly as a JS object\n- **`parseValue()`** — maps `\"true\"/\"false\"/\"null\"` to booleans/null, attempts `std.fmt.parseFloat` for numbers, falls back to string\n- **`stringify()`** — iterates the JS object twice with `jsc.JSPropertyIterator`: first pass emits scalar `key = value\\n` lines, second pass emits `[section]\\n` + sub-key lines; returns via `bun.String.createUTF8ForJS`\n\n### Modifications:\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` after YAMLObject (line ~34) |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | Add `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(...)`, `@export`, `getINIObject` getter, and `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject` import |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI) \\` between `Glob` and `JSON5` (alphabetical order, lines 11–12) |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the hash table near other format parsers |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI { parse(...): Record<string,any>; stringify(...): string; }` with JSDoc after TOML (line ~794) |",
